          {
            "commit": "dd9b9c821c52c6912157a9a6a3f31e354fed9c55",
            "subject": "LU-4349 target: count disconnected exports as stale"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "wang di",
          "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-12-30 16:59:10.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-01-17 23:29:08.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4403 mds: extra lock during resend lock lookup.",
        "message": "LU-4403 mds: extra lock during resend lock lookup.\n\n1. If the request does not require open lock, MDT does not\nneed to search the lock in exp_hash_lock list, because the MDT\nwill release the lock anyway, and it can always re-enqueue the\nrequest during resend.\n\n2. Lock the resource when the MDS is trying to lookup the lock for\nresend request(in mdt_intent_fixup_resent). Otherwise, if the\nlock is being released, fixup_resent will return a released lock,\nwhich will cause LBUG when this lock is being released later.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ice5a75f9a4cc3bcb45f8d54cf809b4a272805804\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/8680\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Mike Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
